#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:4
msgid "How to mark test functions with attributes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:6
msgid ""
"By using the ``pytest.mark`` helper you can easily set metadata on your test "
"functions. You can find the full list of builtin markers in the :ref:`API "
"Reference<marks ref>`. Or you can list all the markers, including builtin "
"and custom, using the CLI - :code:`pytest --markers`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:11
msgid "Here are some of the builtin markers:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:13
msgid ""
":ref:`usefixtures <usefixtures>` - use fixtures on a test function or class"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:14
msgid ""
":ref:`filterwarnings <filterwarnings>` - filter certain warnings of a test "
"function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:15
msgid ":ref:`skip <skip>` - always skip a test function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:16
msgid ""
":ref:`skipif <skipif>` - skip a test function if a certain condition is met"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:17
msgid ""
":ref:`xfail <xfail>` - produce an \"expected failure\" outcome if a certain "
"condition is met"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:19
msgid ""
":ref:`parametrize <parametrizemark>` - perform multiple calls to the same "
"test function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:22
msgid ""
"It's easy to create custom markers or to apply markers to whole test classes "
"or modules. Those markers can be used by plugins, and also are commonly used "
"to :ref:`select tests <mark run>` on the command-line with the :option:`-m` "
"option."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:26
msgid ""
"See :ref:`mark examples` for examples which also serve as documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:30
msgid ""
"Marks can only be applied to tests, having no effect on :ref:`fixtures "
"<fixtures>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:35
msgid "Registering marks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:37
msgid "You can register custom marks in your configuration file like this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:41
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"markers = [\n"
"    \"slow: marks tests as slow (deselect with '-m \\\"not slow\\\"')\",\n"
"    \"serial\",\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:51
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"markers =\n"
"    slow: marks tests as slow (deselect with '-m \"not slow\"')\n"
"    serial"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:58
msgid ""
"Note that everything past the ``:`` after the mark name is an optional "
"description."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:60
msgid ""
"Alternatively, you can register new markers programmatically in a :ref:"
"`pytest_configure <initialization-hooks>` hook:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:63
msgid ""
"def pytest_configure(config):\n"
"    config.addinivalue_line(\n"
"        \"markers\", \"env(name): mark test to run only on named "
"environment\"\n"
"    )"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:71
msgid ""
"Registered marks appear in pytest's help text and do not emit warnings (see "
"the next section). It is recommended that third-party plugins always :ref:"
"`register their markers <registering-markers>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:77
msgid "Raising errors on unknown marks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:79
msgid ""
"Unregistered marks applied with the ``@pytest.mark.name_of_the_mark`` "
"decorator will always emit a warning in order to avoid silently doing "
"something surprising due to mistyped names. As described in the previous "
"section, you can disable the warning for custom marks by registering them in "
"your configuration file or using a custom ``pytest_configure`` hook."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:85
msgid ""
"When the :confval:`strict_markers` configuration option is set, any unknown "
"marks applied with the ``@pytest.mark.name_of_the_mark`` decorator will "
"trigger an error. You can enforce this validation in your project by "
"setting :confval:`strict_markers` in your configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:91
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"addopts = [\"--strict-markers\"]\n"
"markers = [\n"
"    \"slow: marks tests as slow (deselect with '-m \\\"not slow\\\"')\",\n"
"    \"serial\",\n"
"]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/how-to/mark.rst:102
msgid ""
"[pytest]\n"
"strict_markers = true\n"
"markers =\n"
"    slow: marks tests as slow (deselect with '-m \"not slow\"')\n"
"    serial"
msgstr ""
